#### <span id="iv.iii.xii.v-p0.1"></span>Chapter V.

<span id="iv.iii.xii.v-p1"></span>That incentives to all sins spring
from pride.

<span id="iv.iii.xii.v-p2"></span><span class="sc"><span
id="iv.iii.xii.v-p2.1"></span>This</span> is the reason of the first
fall, and the starting point of the original malady, which again
insinuating itself into the first man, <span
id="fr_1019"></span>[1020](#fn_1019.md) through him who had already been
destroyed by it, produced the weaknesses and materials of all faults.
For while he believed that by the freedom of his will and by his own
efforts he could obtain the glory of Deity, he actually lost that glory
which he already possessed through the free gift of the Creator.

